metadata.title: Piper PA-11 Cub Special
aws::graph::propositions: # Piper PA-11 Cub Special Tricycle Landing Gear Modifications
A small number of Piper PA-11s have been modified to use a tricycle landing gear.
The Piper PA-11 was one of the first aircraft to be used by Piper for experiments with the nose wheel configuration.
The nose wheel configuration is also known as tricycle gear.
The original design of the Piper PA-11 is intended to be a tail-dragger.
A modification was created to mount a nose wheel on the Piper PA-11.
The nose wheel is attached to the two rear engine mounts by y-shaped steel tubes.
The y-shaped steel tubes are attached to a steel tube with a shaft.
The shaft slides freely with the wheel.
Cables run underneath the belly directly from fixtures on the rudder pedals to the nose wheel shaft.
The cables gave the ability to steer by pivoting the nose wheel shaft with the rudder pedals.
The shock system consisted of six circular bungee cords located on either side of the nose wheel shaft.
The bungee cords connect to ears on the top tube and the bottom shaft connected to the wheel.
Sometimes four bungee cords were used instead of six for softer landings.

text:
### Modifications

A small number of PA-11s have been modified to use a Tricycle landing gear.
The PA-11 was one of the first aircraft to be used by Piper for experiments with the nose wheel (also known as tricycle gear) configuration. Although its original design is intended to be a tail-dragger, a modification was created to mount a nose wheel. 
The nose wheel is attached to the two rear engine mounts by y-shaped steel tubes attached to a steel tube with a shaft that slides freely with the wheel. Cables run underneath the belly directly from fixtures on the rudder pedals to the nose wheel shaft. This gave the ability to steer by pivoting the nose wheel shaft with the rudder pedals. The shock system consisted of six circular bungee cords, sometimes four for softer landings, located on either side of the nose wheel shaft to ears on the top tube and the bottom shaft connected to the wheel.
